instruction:
Harkamal purchased 8 kg of grapes at the rate of $70 per kg, 9 kg of mangoes at the rate of $60 per kg, 5 kg of apples at the rate of $50 per kg, and 2 kg of oranges at the rate of $30 per kg. The shopkeeper offered the following discounts: 

- 10% discount on the total cost of grapes if the amount is greater than or equal to $400;
- 15% discount on the total cost of mangoes if the amount is greater than or equal to $450;
- 5% discount on the total cost of apples if the amount is greater than or equal to $200;
- No discount on oranges.

Calculate the total amount Harkamal paid to the shopkeeper after applying the respective discounts.

Let $a_n = \begin{cases} 
2^{n-1}, & 1 \leq n \leq 2, n \in \mathbb{N} \\
\frac{1}{3^n}, & n \geq 3, n \in \mathbb{N}
\end{cases}$ be a sequence. Find the limit of the sum of the first $n$ terms of the sequence, $S_n$, as $n$ approaches infinity, i.e., $\lim_{n \to \infty} S_n = \_\_\_\_\_$.

Find the variance of a random variable \( X \) given by the distribution function

$$
F(x)=\left\{
\begin{array}{ccc}
0 & \text{for} & x \leq -2 \\
\frac{x}{4} + \frac{1}{2} & \text{for} & -2 < x \leq 2 \\
1 & \text{for} & x > 2
\end{array}
\right.
$$

In triangle $ABC,$ $a = 7,$ $b = 9,$ and $c = 4.$  Let $I$ be the incenter.

[asy]
unitsize(0.8 cm);

pair A, B, C, D, E, F, I;

B = (0,0);
C = (7,0);
A = intersectionpoint(arc(B,4,0,180),arc(C,9,0,180));
I = incenter(A,B,C);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(incircle(A,B,C));

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
dot("$I$", I, NE);
[/asy]

Then
\[\overrightarrow{I} = x \overrightarrow{A} + y \overrightarrow{B} + z \overrightarrow{C},\]where $x,$ $y,$ and $z$ are constants such that $x + y + z = 1.$  Enter the ordered triple $(x,y,z).$

Given sets A and B defined by the inequalities:

A = {x | x^2 - 3x - 4 <= 0, x in Z}
B = {x | 2x^2 - x - 6 > 0, x in Z}

Find the number of proper subsets of A cap B. Express your answer as a whole number.

