Analyze the following conditions related to the angles of a triangle: 
① $\angle A + \angle B = \angle C$; 
② $\angle A = \angle B = 2\angle C$; 
③ $\angle A : \angle B : \angle C = 1:2:3$. 
Determine the number of conditions that can define the triangle as a right triangle. Express your answer as a numerical value.
